A question we keep hearing about the Covid-19 pandemic: Isn’t this disease a lot like the flu?
A quick unambiguous answer: No, this is not like the seasonal flu.
This is not to downplay the flu; that disease is still an annual blight we could be even more proactive about fighting (annual flu shots are important!).
Some flu seasons are worse than others — but facilities are anticipating flu cases, and prepare for them.
“Which is definitely a problem because the seasonal flu kills 30,000 to 60,000 Americans every year.